
ASP.NET - To log information to the app diagnostics log, use the System.Diagnostics.Trace class

ASP.NET Core apps - To log information to Azure app logs, use the logger factory class
For ASP.NET Core apps on Linux, only "error" messages (levels 4 and 5) are logged.

Node.js apps - app logging is enabled using the console() method

In the portal, app logging is managed from the Diagnostics logs pane of the web app.
Logging to the file system will be automatically reset to Off after 12 hours.

Saving to blob storage is not available for Linux app logs.
When logging to blob storage, you must also set a Retention Period. Unlike the file system logs, blob logs are never deleted by default

